^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|First the bidding. The question is, should Joan bid 2@H? It is really more of a tactical decision. I think 2@H is fine. In general preempting works out well for your side, but there are 2 minuses to Joan preempting.|
PG| ***** 21 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|One is she is a little strong. So it is possible they might miss game. The 2nd is she has 4 spades so they might miss a spade fit. |
PG| ***** 22 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As most of you know, in general I have no problem preempting with an outside 4 card major and if Joan were weaker (make her AJ of clubs the QJ for example) then 2@H is pretty clear despite her 4 spades. But because 1@H is possible and gives their side more flexibility, I might choose 1@H with her hand although 2@H is fine as well.|
PG| ***** 23 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As to whether or not they should be in 4@H. I would say yes even though she only made 3. If one of the black suit finesses work, she makes 4. So it is a good contract.|
PG| ***** 24 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As to whether they get there if she bids 1@H, not. If it goes 1D-1@H-I bid 2@H Bonnie might then bid 3@D (limit raise in hearts) and that might or might not get Joan to bid 4@H.|
PG| ***** 25 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now let's discuss the 1@D bid by Shirley. Many players routinely open 1@D with 4 diamonds and 5 clubs. I very much disagree in general with that approach. If it goes, for example, 1@D-P-1@S-P-2@C, responder will often not know what to do if they cannot be sure how many clubs and how many diamonds opener has. |
PG| ***** 26 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If they have equal length in both minors, which minor should they choose? So I feel, in general, you should open 1@C with 5 clubs and 4 diamonds. However, on this hand, I think 1@D is a good choice with a quality diamond suit and a club suit with no honors, 1 diamond is a good choice.|
PG| ***** 27 ***** |


