NT|^B@2
So what is the right way to play Diamonds? You need to know (all right, make that “guess”) which opponent has the @DQ and to play the suit to finesse against him. So is the play a straightforward 50-50 shot? You just have to guess who has the @DQ and take the finesse through that opponent?|
PG| ***** 165 ***** |


NT|^B@2
The answer is that some “guesses” are better than others. Suppose you choose to play East for the @DQ. You would cash the @DA first (just in case the @DQ fell singleton, ending your problems). Then you lead the @DJ and run it, hoping East has her ladyship. However, when does this play work? If you work it out, in these positions only:|
